@node "Requirements" "Nothing special..."

@{b}*** Requirements ***@{ub}


To run Virus Slayer II you need:
* Amiga ;)
* OS 2.04+
* ReqTools library
* XFD library
* XVS library
* MUI v3.6+
@endnode

@node "Instal" "Any problems?"

@{b}*** Installation ***@{ub}


Copy  libraries  (if  there  are  any  in  the  archive with VS) into LIBS:
directory and VS.prefs into S:  That's all- VS is ready to run.

@endnode

@node "what" "Virus Slayer II is..."

@{b}*** Introduction ***@{ub}


Virus  Slayer  II  is  a  new  virus-killer.   It  is  working  in internal
multitasking (90%).  That means you can view infected files during scanning
operation,  repair  them,  delete  them etc.  It is fast, user-friendly and
highly reliable.  VS II uses xvs.library, so it detects as much viruses, or
even more, as other viruskillers do.

@{b}Features:@{ub}
-file scanning (including decrunching and repairing- XVS and XFD are used)
-memory scanning (uses xvs and internal library with some viruses)
-bootblock checking (uses xvs)
-Arexx port

@endnode

@node "comp" "How to use Virus Slayer II..."

@{b}*** Using Virus Slayer II ***@{ub}


There  is only one window in Virus Slayer II (do you remember VS I and it's
four windows?;)

Remember,  that  it's  BETA version, in full version you will get much more
features.

Beta supports:
Scan group- there you can check files
Results  group- there  you  can  repair, comment and rename infected files
found by Check process
Bootblock Lab- reading, checking and writing bootblocks
Show Virs- viruses recognized by xvs.library
Arexx  port-  with SCAN,REPORT,ICON,GDIRS,GFILES,GCRUNCHED,GVIRS,CLEAR,EXIT
commands


For further help, please use bubble help ;)

That's all. See THINGS TO DO for future improvements.



@endnode

