@node "bugs" " ... ... ... ... ..."

@{b}Bugs@{ub}		


Ahem. ;) Here is the list:

First  of  all, this is BETA version.  It is first application I made using
MUI.   It  is  not finished in 100%.  It works but I have not tested it too
much.

Sometimes  VSII hangs up, I don't know is it my fault- I have some problems
with hardware (my Ami works quite bad in low temp, we have a winter now and
my computer stands near the window ;). Check it out please.

There  are  some problems with listview displaying in the SCAN window- just
change page to RESULTS or iconify VSII.

You  can't stop VSII Check process if you executed it from Arexx.  You have
to wait for it to finish ;/

Future:
-------

-Monitor  tool will be added (HEX,DEC,ASCII dump).  If I could get a source
of any dissassembler, I would add ASM Dump to the view modes
-more gadgets in Results group
-lha/lzx unpack and check
-preferences editor (in few days)
-external checkers (that's good, will be added in few days)
-locale (I need an example in asm)
-new arexx commands

Have a fun! Happy New Year 2000! It is my gift for you...

@endnode

@node "arexx" " Using Arexx... "

@{b}Arexx port@{ub}		


Yes,  Virus  Slayer II has Arexx port.  It was made in about two hours, but
works well. It is named "VSII" and here is the command list:

SCAN PATH/A	-scans given path
-----------
Results:
	RC=0	No viruses found.
	RC=10	Check process found a virus during scanning.
	RC=11 	Unknown error- no argument (I don't know if it is possible,
		but...)
	RC=12	Check already in progress- wait a second.
	RC=13	Path error, select another path.

REPORT FILE/A  -saves content of "Infected" Listview to file.  Structure of
-------------	file is:

		*empty line
		Virus Slayer II Report file
		*empty line
		Infected files:
		*empty line
		path1
		path2
		....
		last path,eof
Results:
	RC=0	Ok
	RC=10	Unknown error ;/
	RC=11	"Infected" listview is empty
	RC=12   File already exists- you have to delete it by yourself, VSII
		is not going to delete other files than viruses
	RC=13	Open error

ICON VS/N	-iconifies/reiconifies VSII main window
---------

	OPtions:			Results:
	VS=0=open VSII window		RC=10
	VS=1=iconify VSII window	RC=11
	VS=2=get VSII window status	RC=current window status- RC=10 for
					opened window or RC=11 for iconified
GDIRS	-get the amount of checked directories
-----
Result:
	RC=number of dirs scanned by Check process

GFILES	-get the amount of checked files
------
Result:
	RC=number of files scanned by Check process

GCRUNCHED	-get the amount of crunchers 
---------
Result:
	RC=number of crunchers found and depacked by Check process 

GVIRS	-get the amount of viruses
-----
Result:
	RC=number of infected files found by Check process

CLEAR	-removes all entries from "Infected" listview
-----
Result:
	RC=0

BOOTCHECK DEVICE/A UNIT/N -checks a bootblock of given device for viruses
---------
Results:
	rc=10	1.3 bootblock
	rc=11	2.0 bootblock
	rc=12	not a dos bootblock
	rc=13	unknown bootblock

	rc=20	VIRUS!!! use install
	rc=21	unknown error! (yeah!)
	rc=22	device read error
	rc=23	device open error

EXIT	-quits VSII without warning
----
Result:
	RC=0


That's  all  about Arexx port of VSII.  It is not much, but...  better that
VS I.

@endnode


